<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-1374] Ability to provide input file with userid, itemid pair</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1374</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently while running the itembased recommender from the command line, user can get recommendation for a particular set of users by using the userFile option or for particular set of itemId&apos;s by using the itemFile option. Using these option together seems to provide recommendations for the cross product for the two inputs. We need an option say userItemFile where a coma separated userid,itemid pair is provide on each line as input and output will be userid,itemid,recommendation. This functionality will be very useful for lot users.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12683255">MAHOUT-1374</key>
            <summary>Ability to provide input file with userid, itemid pair</summary>
